Imam al-Sadiq (AS), when asked to define the ascetic, said, 'The ascetic is the one who renounces the permissible things in this world for fear of having to account for them, and renounces the forbidden things of this world for fear of punishment for them.â€™
[`Auyoun Akhbar al-Ridha (AS), v. 2, p. 52, no. 199]